### ✅ Use this recursive explorer

Here’s a **clean recursive function** to walk any object or array, printing key paths and values:

```js
function deepExplore(obj, path = '', depth = 0, maxDepth = 6) {
  if (depth > maxDepth || obj === null) return;

  for (const key in obj) {
    try {
      const value = obj[key];
      const newPath = path ? `${path}.${key}` : key;

      console.log(newPath, value);

      if (typeof value === 'object' && value !== null) {
        deepExplore(value, newPath, depth + 1, maxDepth);
      }
    } catch (e) {
      console.warn(`Access denied or error at ${key}:`, e);
    }
  }
}
```

### 🧠 Tampermonkey Script: Voice Switcher Prototype

This script assumes:
- You want to fetch **a known message ID** (which you’ll plug in)
- You want to test with a **different voice**, like `onyx`, `shimmer`, etc.

```javascript
// ==UserScript==
// @name         ChatGPT Voice Switcher
// @namespace    https://chatgpt.com/
// @version      0.1
// @description  Play ChatGPT voice responses in different voices from the current session
// @match        https://chatgpt.com/*
// @grant        none
// ==/UserScript==

(async () => {
  // === 🛠 SET YOUR VARIABLES HERE ===
  const conversation_id = '68195939-d2b8-8012-bb96-88231f6ed598';
  const message_id = '<<YOUR_MESSAGE_ID_HERE>>'; // Replace this with actual msg ID
  const voice = 'onyx'; // or 'shimmer', 'nova', 'echo', etc
  const format = 'aac';

  // === 🎧 FETCH + PLAY ===
  const url = `https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/synthesize?message_id=${message_id}&conversation_id=${conversation_id}&voice=${voice}&format=${format}`;

  try {
    const response = await fetch(url);
    if (!response.ok) throw new Error(`Fetch failed: ${response.status}`);
    const blob = await response.blob();
    const audioUrl = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    const audio = new Audio(audioUrl);
    audio.play();
    console.log(`[🎙️] Playing voice "${voice}" for message ${message_id}`);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Voice fetch failed:', err);
  }
})();
```

```js
(() => {
  const YT_LOG_URL = "youtubei/v1/log_event";

  const originalFetch = window.fetch;
  window.fetch = async (...args) => {

  // 🛑 Intercept XHR
  const originalOpen = XMLHttpRequest.prototype.open;
  XMLHttpRequest.prototype.open = function(method, url, ...rest) {
    if (url.includes(YT_LOG_URL)) {
      console.warn("🚫 Blocked YouTube log_event (XHR):", url);
      this.abort(); // kill it outright
      return;
    }
    return originalOpen.call(this, method, url, ...rest);
  };

  console.log("✅ YouTube log_event tracking blocked via fetch + XHR overrides.");
})();
```

### 📦 Option 3: Mass Audio Downloader

Here’s a fetch downloader for local use:

```js
async function downloadAudio(messageId, convoId, voice = "juniper") {
  const url = `https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/synthesize?message_id=${messageId}&conversation_id=${convoId}&voice=${voice}&format=aac`;

  const res = await fetch(url);
  const blob = await res.blob();

  const a = document.createElement("a");
  a.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
  a.download = `${messageId}.aac`;
  a.click();
}
```

**ASSISTANT**: Yep, that’s because **ChatGPT lazily loads messages** as you scroll—only the visible ones (or recently in DOM) have `data-message-id` present.

### 🔄 Fix: Scroll and Extract All Message IDs

You need to **auto-scroll** the page down to load all messages before extracting. Here's a script that:

1. Scrolls to the bottom in intervals.
2. Waits for messages to load.
3. Then extracts all `data-message-id`s.

---

### ✅ Full Scroll + Extract Script:

```js
(async () => {
  const delay = ms => new Promise(res => setTimeout(res, ms));

  // Step 1: Auto-scroll to load all messages
  for (let i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
    window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);
    await delay(500);
    // Exit if bottom reached
    if (window.innerHeight + window.scrollY >= document.body.scrollHeight - 10) break;
  }

  // Step 2: Extract all message IDs
  const messageIds = [...document.querySelectorAll('[data-message-id]')]
    .map(el => el.getAttribute('data-message-id'))
    .filter(Boolean);

  console.log("🧾 All Message IDs:", messageIds);
})();
```

---

### 🔁 Step 1: Scroll and Extract All `data-message-id`s

This script:
- Auto-scrolls the page to load all messages
- Collects all message IDs
- Stores them globally in `window.msgIds` for the next step

```js
(async () => {
  const delay = ms => new Promise(res => setTimeout(res, ms));

  // Auto-scroll
  for (let i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
    window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);
    await delay(500);
    if (window.innerHeight + window.scrollY >= document.body.scrollHeight - 10) break;
  }

  // Collect message IDs
  const msgIds = [...document.querySelectorAll('[data-message-id]')]
    .map(el => el.getAttribute('data-message-id'))
    .filter(Boolean);

  window.msgIds = msgIds;
  console.log("✅ Loaded Message IDs:", msgIds);
})();
```

---

### ▶️ Step 2: Auto-Play All Messages via `fetch` Synth

This one:
- Iterates through `window.msgIds`
- Makes the `fetch` call to the synthesis endpoint
- Streams and plays each response

Replace `"juniper"` with `"echo"`, `"sky"`, etc. for other voices.

```js
(async () => {
  if (!window.msgIds) return console.error("❌ No msgIds found. Run Step 1 first.");

  const conversationId = window.location.pathname.split("/").pop(); // gets current convo ID
  const voice = "juniper";

  for (const msgId of window.msgIds) {
    const url = `https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/synthesize?message_id=${msgId}&conversation_id=${conversationId}&voice=${voice}&format=aac`;
    
    try {
      const response = await fetch(url, {
        method: 'GET',
        credentials: 'include',
        headers: {
          'Authorization': document.cookie.match(/__Secure-accessToken=(.*?)(;|$)/)?.[1]
            ? `Bearer ${decodeURIComponent(document.cookie.match(/__Secure-accessToken=(.*?)(;|$)/)[1])}`
            : '', // fallback blank
        }
      });

      const blob = await response.blob();
      const audio = new Audio(URL.createObjectURL(blob));
      await audio.play();

      // wait until audio finishes
      await new Promise(resolve => {
        audio.onended = resolve;
      });

    } catch (e) {
      console.warn("⚠️ Failed for message:", msgId, e);
    }
  }

  console.log("✅ Done playing all messages.");
})();
```

### 🔐 Note:
- Works only if you're authenticated with access to voice synth.
- `__Secure-accessToken` must be present in cookies (you may not need to manually extract unless you’re scripting outside the ChatGPT domain).

### ✅ Full Script: Scrape All Messages, Fetch Audio, Store Blobs

```js
(async () => {
  const voice = "juniper";
  const convoId = window.location.pathname.split("/").pop();
  const token = decodeURIComponent(document.cookie.match(/__Secure-accessToken=(.*?)(;|$)/)[1]);

  // Step 1: Extract message IDs from DOM (top-down)
  const msgEls = [...document.querySelectorAll('[data-message-id]')];
  const msgIds = msgEls.map(el => el.dataset.messageId).filter(Boolean);

  console.log(`🎯 Found ${msgIds.length} message IDs.`);

  // Step 2: Fetch audio blobs
  const audioBlobs = [];

  for (const id of msgIds) {
    try {
      const res = await fetch(
        `https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/synthesize?message_id=${id}&conversation_id=${convoId}&voice=${voice}&format=aac`,
        {
          method: "GET",
          credentials: "include",
          headers: {
            Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`
          }
        }
      );

      if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Status ${res.status}`);

      const blob = await res.blob();
      audioBlobs.push({ id, blob });
      console.log(`✅ Retrieved audio for ${id}`);
    } catch (err) {
      console.warn(`⚠️ Failed to fetch audio for ${id}`, err);
    }
  }

  console.log(`🎧 Fetched ${audioBlobs.length} audio files.`);

  // Step 3: Optional ZIP download
  const zipEnabled = true;
  if (zipEnabled) {
    const zip = new JSZip();
    audioBlobs.forEach(({ id, blob }) => {
      zip.file(`${id}.aac`, blob);
    });

    const zipBlob = await zip.generateAsync({ type: "blob" });
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(zipBlob);
    const a = document.createElement("a");
    a.href = url;
    a.download = `${convoId}_voices.zip`;
    a.click();
    console.log("📦 Download triggered: voices.zip");
  } else {
    console.log("🛑 ZIP disabled – blobs stored in memory:", audioBlobs);
  }
})();
```

### 🧠 **Tampermonkey Setup**

1. **Install Tampermonkey** (if you haven’t): [https://www.tampermonkey.net](https://www.tampermonkey.net)
2. Create a new script and paste the following:

```javascript
// ==UserScript==
// @name         ChatGPT Message ID Collector
// @namespace    http://tampermonkey.net/
// @version      1.0
// @description  Collect all ChatGPT message IDs and prep for export
// @author       You
// @match        https://chatgpt.com/*
// @grant        none
// @require      https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jszip@3.10.1/dist/jszip.min.js
// ==/UserScript==

(function() {
  'use strict';

  function getAllMessageIDs() {
    const nodes = document.querySelectorAll('[data-message-id]');
    const ids = [...nodes].map(n => n.getAttribute('data-message-id'));
    const uniqueIDs = [...new Set(ids)].filter(Boolean);
    console.log('✅ Collected message IDs:', uniqueIDs);
    return uniqueIDs;
  }

  function downloadJSON(data, filename = 'chatgpt-message-ids.json') {
    const blob = new Blob([JSON.stringify(data, null, 2)], { type: 'application/json' });
    const a = document.createElement('a');
    a.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    a.download = filename;
    a.click();
  }

  window.collectChatGPTIDs = () => {
    const ids = getAllMessageIDs();
    downloadJSON(ids);
  };

  console.log('✅ Script loaded. Type `collectChatGPTIDs()` in the console to collect and download.');
})();
```

### ✅ **Working Fix Script: Fetch + Audio Blob Playback**

Paste this in the **dev console** on the ChatGPT site **while logged in**:

```javascript
const msgIDs = [
  "f9847a1b-9d99-4ffe-a18f-0eea21583d95",
  "f6ac2013-79d8-49fc-b4bb-ea23cd58a067",
  // ... add the rest from your file
];

const voice = 'juniper';
const delay = 2500;

async function playWithAuth(messageId) {
  const url = `/backend-api/synthesize?message_id=${messageId}&voice=${voice}&format=aac`;
  try {
    const response = await fetch(url, {
      method: "GET",
      credentials: "include", // use current cookies/session
    });
    if (!response.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${response.status}`);
    const blob = await response.blob();
    const audio = new Audio(URL.createObjectURL(blob));
    audio.play();
    console.log(`🔊 Playing: ${messageId}`);
    return new Promise(resolve => audio.onended = resolve);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(`❌ Error playing ${messageId}:`, err);
    return Promise.resolve();
  }
}

(async () => {
  for (const id of msgIDs) {
    await playWithAuth(id);
    await new Promise(res => setTimeout(res, delay)); // slight gap between clips
  }
})();
```

### 🔍 Why You're Getting `401 Unauthorized`

The `401` errors when hitting `/synthesize` like this:

```
GET https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/synthesize?message_id=...&voice=juniper&format=aac 401 (Unauthorized)
```

...mean the request is missing **a valid session token** or the **OpenAI JWT bearer token** used for secure API endpoints (like TTS). It doesn’t matter if you can play it via UI — when you try to `fetch()` it directly, it requires a **live authenticated session**, with:

- `authorization: Bearer ...` from current valid login
- `oai-device-id`, `oai-language`, and other headers
- Plus possibly cookie-based session proof

You can't just replay these fetches unless the browser context is still authenticated **and** your script is running in a privileged (trusted) execution context like a browser extension or DevTools snippet injected in the same tab/session.

---

### ✅ Updated DevTools Script – Sequential Voice Playback

```js
const msgIDs = [
  "f9847a1b-9d99-4ffe-a18f-0eea21583d95",
  "f6ac2013-79d8-49fc-b4bb-ea23cd58a067",
  "0dd51153-9274-4be0-8a66-5d00bc6ef5d8",
  // ...add the rest of your message IDs here
];

async function playAllVoices() {
  for (const id of msgIDs) {
    console.log("🔊 Playing message ID:", id);
    const audio = new Audio(`/backend-api/synthesize?message_id=${id}&voice=juniper&format=aac`);

    try {
      await audio.play();
      await new Promise(res => {
        audio.onended = res;
        audio.onerror = () => {
          console.error("❌ Error playing:", id);
          res();
        };
      });
    } catch (err) {
      console.error(`❌ Failed to play ${id}:`, err);
    }

    // Optional pause between plays (in ms)
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
  }

  console.log("✅ All messages played.");
}

playAllVoices();
```

- ✅ Requires you to be actively logged in and on the correct `chatgpt.com` page.
- ✅ Leverages `<audio>` so it inherits your authenticated cookies/session.
- 🔊 It will play one message at a time, respecting the `.onended` signal.
- 🔁 You can paste your entire full ID array into `msgIDs`.
